  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Country Micro Projects Scheme</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ICMPS supports projects that address the root causes of poverty and injustice in a way that is strategic and cost effective, enhance local capacity and ownership, have a focus on the poorest of the poor and are consistent with other programmes of work funded by Irish Aid in the countries concerned. Fifteen Missions currently participate in the scheme: Abuja, Amman, Ankara, Bangkok, Beijing, Bogota, Brasilia, Buenos Aires, Cairo, Canberra, Jakarta, Mexico, New Delhi, Shanghai, and Wellington.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The In Country Micro Projects Scheme (ICMPS) enables Irish diplomatic missions in a number of countries, where Ireland does not have a development programme, to allocate funds to local civil society organisations for small development projects.</narrative>
  </description>
